More than 58% of the world's coral reefs are endangered due to pollution, over-harvesting, and human activities, as per the World Conservation Union (IUCN).
The IUCN will release a detailed report on this next month.
Human impacts, climate change, and introduced species like starfish are major factors in reef destruction.
Poverty and population growth exacerbate the issue in South Asia.
Recovery from damage caused by El Nino is slow.
Artificial reefs are being created to enhance fishery resources.
The coral reefs face a long road to recovery, with global warming posing a significant threat.
